Leeds United striker Patrick Bamford will miss the club’s relegation decider at Brentford after testing positive for COVID-19. The West Yorkshire club need to better Burnley’s result against Newcastle in order to survive. Bamford, 28, has suffered an injury-hit campaign, only featuring in nine games and scoring twice. -Advertisement- He has suffered separate ankle, hamstring, and foot injuries. Last season, he scored 17 times in 38 appearances. Leeds have also endured injuries to crucial players Kalvin Phillips and Liam Cooper, which leaves them in 18th ahead of kick-off. Speaking ahead of kick-off, head coach Jesse Marsch said: “Firstly, he was fit and ready to go and then two days ago, he tested positive for COVID-19, and he’s been really, really sick and not been able to get out of bed. “Obviously, it’s unfortunate for him and us. He wasn’t in a position to travel.” A loss on Sunday afternoon will send Leeds back to the Championship after a two-year stay in the Premier League. They spent 16 years in the second division between 2004 and 2020. POLL Leeds have named their youngest starting XI of the season for the fixture.